<title>JAPAN: Japan May silver imports surge by 59.5 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Japan May silver imports surge by 59.5 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's silver imports in May surged by 59.5 percent from a year earlier to 78.45 tonnes, Ministry of Finance (MOF) data released on Friday showed.</p>
<p>The figures released by MOF were as follows (in tonnes):</p>
<p>		     May 97	Apr 97	May 96</p>
<p> Total		78.45	182.86	49.14</p>
<p>Major suppliers:</p>
<p> Mexico	     17.99	 54.67	18.01</p>
<p>Cumulative imports in the first five months of 1997 totalled 601.84 tonnes against 451.39 tonnes in the same period a year earlier.-- Tokyo Commodity Desk +81-3-3432-7431</p>
